> — Research Diver 09, Log 14-A  

> “Its eyes aren’t eyes. They’re windows looking back at the surface from somewhere deeper than water.”  
> — Sonar Technician, Station Pelagos  

> “ERP node 7 failed for 43 seconds. The silence afterward was worse than the hum.”  
> — Operator-Δ13  

---

## ETHICAL CONSIDERATIONS
- **Do not** deploy lethal payloads against Leviathane. Aggressive frequencies may provoke a surfacing cascade.  
- **Do not** store resonance recordings on unsecured media; playback may trigger minor summoning effects.  
- **Do** maintain psychological rotation among marine operators; recurrent dreams of drowning are predictive of breach.  

---

## RESEARCH RECOMMENDATIONS
- Study Leviathane’s bioacoustic structure — it may encode non-human communication.  
- Investigate the link between urban entropy and abyssal surfacing probability.  
- Examine whether deep-sea ruins beneath Urbanshade act as amplification conduits.  
- Expand ERP capacity to include adaptive thermal modulation.  

---

## FINAL NOTE
Leviathane is not a monster — it is a mirror. It rises when the surface forgets what lies beneath it.  
Our machines hum to keep it dreaming. Our cities stay lit to convince the dark it has no place here.  

